#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:11-3
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Braille_Math_Editor.htm+html.body.h1:11-3"
msgid "Braille Math Editor"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:12-3
msgid ""
"If you have access to a Braille display that also supports typing in Braille "
"and you are familiar with the Nemeth or UEB Math code for entering and "
"reading math content, the JAWS Braille Math Editor enables you to input your "
"own equations, and in Office 365, edit existing equations in Word documents."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:13-1
msgid ""
"To open the Math Editor, press the layered command <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</"
"strong> followed by <strong>SHIFT+EQUALS</strong> (plus sign). Focus braille "
"display users can also press <strong>DOTS 3-4-6-7 CHORD</strong>. Similar to "
"reading math content, JAWS braille output must be set for one of the English "
"Grade 1 or Grade 2 translation settings in order to launch the editor."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:14-1
msgid ""
"When the Math Editor opens, focus is placed into an edit field where you can "
"immediately begin typing the equation using Nemeth or UEB Math from your "
"braille display’s keyboard. To switch between Braille math codes, press "
"<strong>INSERT+EQUALS</strong>, or <strong>RIGHT SHIFT+DOTS 1-2-3-4-5-6</"
"strong> from a Focus Braille display. As you type, a preview pane below the "
"edit field visually displays the equation so a sighted teacher or parent can "
"review it. Once you are finished inputting the math equation, press "
"<strong>ENTER</strong> or choose the Accept button to close the Math Editor. "
"If you are in Word, the equation you entered is automatically inserted into "
"the document at your current location. The equation is also copied to the "
"Clipboard so you can paste it in other applications."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:15-1
msgid ""
"Opening the Math Editor while focused on a math equation in a Word document "
"displays the existing equation in the editor using the currently active "
"Braille math code, allowing you to edit or replace it. After making any "
"changes and pressing <strong>ENTER</strong> to close the editor, the current "
"equation in the document is replaced by the new or modified equation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:16-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> After inserting or modifying an equation in Word from "
"the Math Editor, the blinking cursor (dots 7 and 8) on the Braille display "
"always remains at the beginning of the math content, even as you move by "
"character with the <strong>LEFT</strong> and <strong>RIGHT ARROW</strong> "
"keys. If you need to insert another line of math content, first press the "
"<strong>END</strong> key to move to the end of the current math content and "
"then press <strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:17-1
msgid ""
"While the Math Editor is opened, you have the following additional options:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:19-3
msgid "Press <strong>CTRL+N</strong> to start a new equation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:20-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>CTRL+P</strong> to preview the current equation in the Math "
"Viewer. When finished, press <strong>ESC</strong> to return to the Math "
"Editor."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CBraille_Math_Editor.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:21-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>ALT+E</strong> to open the edit menu where you can copy your "
"Braille input to the Clipboard using a specific format. MathML is the "
"default format when copying, however, depending on the application where you "
"intend to paste the equation, you can also choose to copy your content to "
"LaTeX or Braille ASCII. After choosing a format to copy to, paste the "
"equation into the specific application before pressing <strong>ENTER</"
"strong> or selecting Accept to close the Math Editor as this always copies "
"as MathML and will erase the current clipboard contents."
msgstr ""

